        "name": "Tides of the Aether",
        "textElements": [
            {
                "regularText": "During combat the Priest deepens his connection with the Aether and they use that connection to empower their spells or other magical abilities.<br>During the battle you will aquimulate Aether Dice which are d6. These dice represent the current Aether dice pool, the lower the value the more they represent good and the higher the values the more they represent Evil. During the battle these dice can change and additional dice are added.",
                "headerLine": null,
                "bulletPoints": null,
                "ability": null
            },
            {
                "regularText": null,
                "headerLine": null,
                "bulletPoints": [
                    "At the start of each of the Priestâ€™s turn he receives ona Aether dice of random value.",
                    "Falling Unconcious removes all current Aether Dice."
                ],
                "ability": null
            },
            {
                "regularText": null,
                "headerLine": "Alignment",
                "bulletPoints": null,
                "ability": null
            },
            {
                "regularText": "The Priest also gains additional Aether Dice depending on their Allignment",
                "headerLine": null,
                "bulletPoints": null,
                "ability": null
            },
            {
                "regularText": null,
                "headerLine": null,
                "bulletPoints": [
                    "<span class=\"fw-bold\">Good: </span>The first time during a [ROUND] you heal an ally or grant a positive status effect, you gain one Aether Dice equal to d3.",
                    "<span class=\"fw-bold\">Evil: </span>The first time during a [ROUND] you damage an enemy or inflict a negative status effect on them you gain one Aether Dice equal d3+3." ,
                    "<span class=\"fw-bold\">Lawful: </span>The first time during a [ROUND] you succeed a [SAVE] or remove a status effect from a creature you gain one Aether Dice you already have, if you have none none you can choose one.",
                    "<span class=\"fw-bold\">Chaotic: </span>The first time during a [ROUND] you turn a [D20 TEST] from a failure to a success or from a success to a failure, you gain a random aether dice.",
                    "<span class=\"fw-bold\">Partial Neutral: </span>You can trigger the ability of your other allignment twice per [ROUND].",
                    "<span class=\"fw-bold\">True Neutral: </span>You gain an additional Aether Dice at the start of your Turn."
                ],
                "ability": null
            },
            {
                "regularText": null,
                "headerLine": "Aether Dice Notation",
                "bulletPoints": null,
                "ability": null
            },
            {
                "regularText": "The following Notation is used for describing Aether Dice (AD) and desired Values:",
